    {
      "reviewerId": null,
      "reviewerUrl": null,
      "name": null,
      "reviewerNumberOfReviews": 4,
      "isLocalGuide": false,
      "reviewerPhotoUrl": null,
      "text": "Dad had oral chemo a few months back, but his recovery wasn't going as planned. He was still really unsteady and had experienced bad falls at home that scared us all. None of us could take extended time off work to supervise his recovery properly.\nAustin Royal has been exactly what we needed. These people really know their stuff when it comes to case like my dad. The physio team worked wonders with Dad's mobility, and they made sure he was eating the right foods and taking his meds on schedule. They even suggested some supplements that helped with his bone healing.\nThe whole setup is just so professional yet welcoming. Super clean facilities, well-organized visiting times so it never feels chaotic, and the staff genuinely cares about each patient's progress.\nWatching Dad get his confidence back has been amazing. His walking has improved so much, and more importantly, he feels safe and secure there. No more falls, and his strength is definitely coming back. Our whole family can finally breathe easy knowing he's in such good hands.\n\nThanks, Ms Lim.",
